LORE kowloon-priest
FLAGS KOWLOON PRIEST
- Temple Circle healers wear undyed linen; answer to no secular authority
  while treating patients — a Neon Covenant privilege, never revoked
- Funerary rites without discrimination of origin or faction; established
  during the Ashfall years; non-negotiable
- Eastern corridors: thaumaturgic exchange for spent spell components, enchant-
  ment residue salvage, and reagents; Temple Circle monitors closely
- Temple-witnessed oaths have civil standing without requiring the Magistracy
  jade seal
- Oral records extend to the Lampkeeper era before the Covenant; the Temple
  Circle holds the city's oldest institutional memory
- Deltari ancestral shrine maintenance is a Temple Circle responsibility;
  they handle flood-memorial services for Yen-Mak and other lost settlements
~
